  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2018-08-23",
    "date": "2019-09-04T19:55:54Z",
    "text": "E-Verify System Act of 2018\n\nThis bill (1) directs the Department of Homeland Security to develop an electronic employment eligibility verification system modeled after E-Verify and phases in the mandatory use of such a system, (2) directs the Social Security Administration to begin work toward the issuance of fraud-resistant and tamper-resistant Social Security cards, and (3) establishes the Office of the Small Business and Employee Advocate to assist small businesses and individuals to comply with employment-related immigration laws."
  },
